  "doc_id": "5941",
  "text": "The care of cerebrovascular patients is becoming more integrated in terms of treatment strategies, location of care, and even providers. Potential areas for further development include better integration of the radiographic images and reconstructions with the microscope via more advanced heads-up displays. The enhancement of image quality by a variety of postprocessing techniques has progressed significantly in recent years and should continue. Examples include metallic artifact reduction and region of interest analysis, which can be combined to produce remarkably vivid images despite the presence of dense metal objects. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] These emerging technologies available with Siemens and other angiography equipment can help visualize AVMs and differentiate residual lesion and embolisate. ",
